# Hub runtime state. All of it regenerates -- `python run.py --reset` rebuilds
# data/ from scratch, which is what you want before a demo anyway. Ignore the
# whole directory: SQLite also writes -wal/-shm siblings and the checkpoint
# rotates to .1/.2/.3, and none of those match a *.db or *.ckpt pattern.
data/
hub.out
hub.err
p1.out
p1.err
*.ckpt
*.ckpt.[0-9]
*.onnx
spool.jsonl

